President Obama has nominated Steven Nathan Berk and Judge Elizabeth Carroll Wingo to serve on the Superior Court of the District of Columbia. Berk is a principal and founder of Berk Law, where he focuses on consumer protection issues and represents whistleblowers. He has previous experience as an Assistant United States Attorney and as a staff attorney for the Securities and Exchange Commission. Berk received his J.D. from Boston College Law School. Judge Wingo has been serving as a Magistrate Judge on the Superior Court since 2006. She previously worked as Chief of the Criminal Section in the Office of the Attorney General for the District of Columbia. She also served as an Assistant United States Attorney and as a law clerk for a federal judge. Judge Wingo obtained her J.D. from Yale Law School. President Obama expressed confidence in both nominees' ability to serve with integrity and a commitment to justice.